    name: "Cholesterinum",
    abbrev: "Chol.",
    category: "plant",
    intro: "Cholesterine--The proximate principle--Furnished by the epithelium lining of gall bladder and the larger ducts For cancer of the liver. Obstinate hepatic engorgements. Burning pain in side; on walking holds his hand on side, hurts him so. Opacities of the vitreous. Jaundice; gallstones. Cholesterine is the physiological opponent of Lecithin. Both seem to play some unknown part in the growth of tum",
    sections: {},
