    sections: {"Mouth": "Ulceration of tongue, gums and mouth; aphthae. Burning in mouth, throat and stomach.", "Stool": "Loose, windy, dark stool, immediately after dinner. Burning in anus. Dark, bilious, offensive diarrhoea, with sallow complexion.", "Skin": "Vesicular eczema of face in infants, with nursing sore mouth."},
