    name: "Jonesia Asoka",
    abbrev: "Jon.",
    category: "plant",
    intro: "Bark of an Indian Tree, introduced by Dr. ND Ray, Calcutta (JONOSIA ASOCA) Has extensive sphere of action on female organs. Amenorrhoea and metrorrhagia.",
    sections: {"Head": "Unilateral headache; reflex uterine, congestive headache, better open air and by free flow. Pain in eyeballs; supraorbital pains, photophobia. Nasal catarrh, profuse, watery discharge. Loss of sense of smell.", "Gastric": "Desire for sweets, also acid things. Thirsty, excessive nausea; obstinate constipation, haemorrhoids.", "Female": "Delayed and irregular menses; menstrual colic; amenorrhoea, pain in ovaries before flow; menorrhagia, irritable bladder; leucorrhoea.", "Sleep": "Disturbed. Dreams of travelling.", "Back": "Pain along spine radiating to abdomen and thighs."},
    keynotes: ["Bark of an Indian Tree, introduced by Dr", "ND Ray, Calcutta (JONOSIA ASOCA) Has extensive sphere of action on female organs", "Amenorrhoea and metrorrhagia"],
