    sections: {"Head": "Vertigo when moving slowly. Sensation as if he had forgotten something. The head seems full of blood. Convulsions and epilepsy from suppressed menses. Piercing thrusts of pain.", "Nose": "Nosebleed (Erecht). Piercing pain from eyes to root of nose.", "Stool": "Haemorrhage from bowels. Bleeding haemorrhoids. Urine bloody (Senec aur).", "Female": "Menses early, profuse, protracted. Haemorrhage from uterus; bright red, fluid. Painful varices during pregnancy.", "Respiratory": "Haemoptysis in incipient phthisis. Cough, with bloody expectoration, in suppressed menses or haemorrhoids. Violent palpitation."},
