    sections: {"Head": "Anxious, furious, disposed to fight. Headache better by vomiting. Ringing in ears.", "Mouth": "Ulcerative inflammation of mouth. Tongue red or bluish-red. Coated.", "Stomach": "Loss of appetite. Obstinate constipation.", "Respiratory": "Persistent choking cough with copious expectoration. Hoarseness, constriction of chest. Difficult breathing.", "Female": "Fluor albus. Debility."},
    keynotes: ["Sulphurous Acid", "H2 S O3 Sulphurous acid, (tonsillitis (as a spray), acne rosacea, ulcerative stomatitis, pityriasis versicolor)"],
