    intro: "Wild Thyme Respiratory infections of children; dry nervous asthma, whooping-cough, severe spasms but little sputum. Ringing in ears with feeling of pressure in head. Burning in pharynx, sore, throat worse empty swallowing; blood vessels distended, dark.",
    sections: {},
